parameters.text:
=JOB TITLE: {{ $json.title }}

JOB DESCRIPTION:
{{ $json.description }}

JOB METADATA:
- Budget: {{ $json.budget || 'Not specified' }}
- Experience Level: {{ $json.experience_level || 'Not specified' }}
- Hours/Week: {{ $json.hours_week || 'Not specified' }}
- Duration: {{ $json.duration || 'Not specified' }}
- Type: {{ $json.job_type || 'Not specified' }}

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
{{ $json.candidate_profile }}

CRITICAL: The attention_test field is for INFORMATION ONLY — it tells us what to include in the proposal. It is NEVER a reason to reject a match. Do NOT set is_match to false because of an attention test. Evaluate the job purely on skills, experience, budget, and industry alignment.

Evaluate this Upwork job against the candidate profile. Return JSON only.

=JOB TITLE: {{ $('Set: Candidate Profile').item.json.title }}

JOB DESCRIPTION:
{{ $('Set: Candidate Profile').item.json.description }}

JOB URL: {{ $('Set: Candidate Profile').item.json.url }}

MATCH ANALYSIS:
- Score: {{ $json.output.match_score }}/100
- Reason: {{ $json.output.reason }}
- Suggested Rate: ${{ $json.output.suggested_rate }}/hr
- Attention Test: {{ $json.output.attention_test || 'None' }}

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
{{ $('Set: Candidate Profile').item.json.candidate_profile }}

Write a winning Upwork proposal for this job.

parameters.jsCode:
const proposal = $input.first().json;
const setData = $('Set: Candidate Profile').first().json;
const filterData = $('AI: Job Filter').first().json;
const draftText = (proposal.text || proposal.output || '').trim();

return [{
  json: {
    record_id: setData.record_id,
    draft_proposal: draftText,
    match_score: filterData.output?.match_score || 0,
    match_reason: filterData.output?.reason || '',
    suggested_rate: filterData.output?.suggested_rate || 65,
    attention_test: filterData.output?.attention_test || ''
  }
}];

